{"id":"project-LICHEN-kpag","title":"KISS transport: ring buffer overflow not tracked in stats","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/kiss_transport.c
Lines: 362-369

In uart_rx_callback(), when the ring buffer overflows, it only logs a warning but doesn't track it in statistics:

    if (written == 0) {
        LOG_WRN("KISS RX: ring buffer overflow");
        // Missing: ctx->stats.overflow_errors++;
    }

Compare with the SLIP transport (slip_transport.c line 358-360) which has the same pattern - overflow is logged but not counted.

The overflow_errors field exists in kiss_transport_stats (line 126 of header) but is only incremented in the RX thread (line 402-403), not in the ISR where the actual overflow occurs.

Fix: Increment overflow_errors in the ISR when ring_buf_put returns 0. Note: must be careful with synchronization since this is ISR context.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:53:58.688011Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:53:58.688037Z"}
